# Customer Billing Analysis

## Objective
Analyze customer billing data to identify unbilled accounts, common billing errors, and process inefficiencies impacting customer experience.

## Tools Used
- SQL
- Microsoft Excel

## Skills Demonstrated
- Data cleaning and validation
- SQL aggregation and filtering
- KPI development
- Root cause analysis
- Business insight generation
- Data visualization

## Dataset
Simulated billing dataset including customer account status, payment history, billing errors, issue types, and resolution times.

## Process
- Cleaned and standardized raw billing data in Excel
- Queried dataset using SQL to identify high-frequency billing issues
- Calculated KPIs such as error rate, average resolution time, and unbilled account percentage
- Built Excel dashboard with Pivot Tables and charts to visualize trends

## Key Insights
- Billing errors accounted for approximately 35% of unresolved customer cases
- Missing enrollment information was the leading cause of unbilled accounts
- Accounts with billing errors took 2.4x longer to resolve on average
- A small number of issue categories generated the majority of support workload

## Outcome
Delivered a dashboard and analytical summary to support data-driven improvements in billing accuracy, reduce resolution time, and lower repeat customer contacts.
